# Maintainarr — Environment configuration example
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Environment file loading hierarchy (highest priority first):
#
#   .env.{NODE_ENV}.local   ← gitignored — your personal overrides for a specific env
#   .env.local              ← gitignored — your personal base overrides (skipped in test)
#   .env.{NODE_ENV}         ← committed  — shared defaults for a specific env
#   .env                    ← committed  — shared base defaults
#
# Copy this file to .env and uncomment the values you want to change.
# For secrets, create .env.local (it is gitignored and will never be committed).
#
# In production, inject environment variables directly via your platform
# (Docker, systemd, Kubernetes, etc.) — .env files are not loaded if the
# variable is already present in process.env.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Server ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NODE_ENV=development
# PORT=5057
# COMMIT_TAG=local

# ── Logging ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# LOG_LEVEL=info               # error | warn | info | http | verbose | debug | silly
# LOG_DIR=./config/logs

# ── Database ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# DB_PATH=./config/db/maintainarr.db   # use :memory: for ephemeral/test
# DB_LOGGING=false

# ── Network ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# TRUST_PROXY=false            # set true when behind nginx / Caddy / etc.

# ── TMDB ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required for backdrop images on the login page.
# Get a free API key at https://www.themoviedb.org/settings/api
# TMDB_API_KEY=

# ── Session ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required in production. A random secret is generated automatically in
# development but sessions will not persist across restarts.
# Generate a strong secret: node -e "console.log(require('crypto').randomBytes(32).toString('hex'))"
# SESSION_SECRET=
